article.headline: Stony Brook 60, Hartford 37
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- Bryan Drougher scored 23 points and Stony Brook (12-7, 7-1) never trailed in a 60-37 rout of Hartford Wednesday night in America East Conference action. Drougher was the lone Stony Brook player in double figures, but that hadly mattered. Not on a night when 10 different Seawolves scored while Hartford (4-16, 4-4) shot so poorly. Genesis Maciel was the only Hawk in double figures, coming off the bench to score 10 points. Collectively, Hartford made just 13 of 42 field goal attempts (31 percent). The Hawks were a horrid 3 for 20 from beyond the 3-point arc, Maciel hitting two of those treys. Stony Brook, meanwhile, the America East leader, connected on 22 of 42 shots from the floor, including 9 of 18 3-pointers. Five of those treys were by Dougher. Up 24-18 at intermission, the Seawolves led by as many as 25 points in the second half.
